<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53046e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53046e">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53046e"> 46(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Familien &amp; Taufname / = flowers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Linnaeus had undertaken the police task to provide every plant with a proper noun by giving it an identity, that is a family and a first name [<i>dass er ihr einen <mark>Familiennamen und einen Taufnamen</mark> beilegte</i>]</font>, whereas earlier botanists had actually given a description rather than a name to the plants they knew.] <small> Fritz Mauthner, <a name="FMBK1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FMBK1"><cite title="source">Beitr&auml;ge zu einer Kritik der Sprache.</cite></a> 3 vols (1901-2) III 508</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Turquoise ink. </mm> </dd></dl>
